text: My bad. You already said that.

It’s the implied order of when those abilities will be relevant. “This costs less” or “can only cast this if” and such would be the first info you need to know. Keywords affect how it behaves in play so those go near the top as well. Any ETB would follow, any static abilities after, and death effects or abilities that work from the grave would be last. Template follows the assumed life cycle of the card if it’s played normally.
That makes sense
It makes sense logically, too. Visually though I want to scan that first line for keywords, particularly when the card is upside down across the table.

first article starts with Boros Reckoner and shows how just using the synergy ratings on EDH Rec you can go from "this is a pretty cool card for my aggressive deck that plays Blasphemous Act" to "I have built an entire deck around blowing someone out with red sweepers and damage redirection"
or anywhere in between

Probably not mindblowing to people who've spent a lot of years building EDH decks and finding corner cases, but there's a lot of spots where cards that synergise with eachother aren't well known or easy to find by searching keywords, and I wanted to highlight how useful EDHREC is as a resource for finding those hidden connections
